<p><b>Stigler's law of eponymy</b> is a process proposed by <a href="/wiki/University_of_Chicago" title="University of Chicago">University of Chicago</a> <a href="/wiki/Statistics" title="Statistics">statistics</a> professor <a href="/wiki/Stephen_Stigler" title="Stephen Stigler">Stephen Stigler</a> in his 1980 publication "Stigler’s law of eponymy" <sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup>. In its simplest and strongest form it says: <b>"No scientific discovery is named after its original discoverer."</b></p>
